<Link id="l01550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1550"><Highlight kind="normal">    std::optional&lt;AddressRangeValuePair&gt; CurrRange;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1551"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1552"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// FIXME: This logic is meant to generate exactly the same output as</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1553"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Darwin&#39;s classic dsymutil. There is a nicer way to implement this</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1554"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// by simply putting all the relocated line info in NewRows and simply</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01555" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1555"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// sorting NewRows before passing it to emitLineTableForUnit. This</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01556" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1556"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// should be correct as sequences for a function should stay</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01557" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1557"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// together in the sorted output. There are a few corner cases that</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01558" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1558"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// look suspicious though, and that required to implement the logic</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01559" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1559"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// this way. Revisit that once initial validation is finished.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01561" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1561"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Iterate over the object file line info and extract the sequences</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01562" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1562"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// that correspond to linked functions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01563" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1563"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/dwarfdebugline/row">DWARFDebugLine::Row</a> Row : InputLineTable-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/dwarfdebugline/linetable/#a08f2df6a1aaacec42c6ded0585a11e4d">Rows</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01564" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1564"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Check whether we stepped out of the range. The range is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01565" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1565"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// half-open, but consider accept the end address of the range if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01566" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1566"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// it is marked as end&#95;sequence in the input (because in that</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01567" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1567"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// case, the relocation offset is accurate and that entry won&#39;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01568" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1568"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// serve as the start of another function).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01569" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1569"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (!CurrRange || !CurrRange-&gt;Range.contains(Row.Address.Address)) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1570"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We just stepped out of a known range. Insert a end&#95;sequence</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1571"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// corresponding to the end of the range.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1572"><Highlight kind="normal">        uint64&#95;t StopAddress =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1573"><Highlight kind="normal">            CurrRange ? CurrRange-&gt;Range.end() + CurrRange-&gt;Value : -1ULL;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1574"><Highlight kind="normal">        CurrRange = FunctionRanges.getRangeThatContains(Row.Address.Address);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1575"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (StopAddress != -1ULL &amp;&amp; !Seq.empty()) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1576"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Insert end sequence row with the computed end address, but</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1577"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the same line as the previous one.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1578"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> NextLine = Seq.back();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1579"><Highlight kind="normal">          NextLine.Address.Address = StopAddress;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1580"><Highlight kind="normal">          NextLine.EndSequence = 1;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1581"><Highlight kind="normal">          NextLine.PrologueEnd = 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
